Tags.string 'NodeComment': This is an overwriteable function in game mode. We do not want the exsiting framework to handle it but do something own here
Spawn a new player at the active spawn pad. Give him an index between 0 and max bots. GetMaxBots is a pure library function we can call from anywhere.

Initilize the save game handling in the game instance via an interface. 
The reason for calling it her is the fact that the init event in the game instance is too early. The world doesnt exist. But we need the world context to do what we need to do in the save game. Check the game instance for more details.

In the game mode we mainly handle the player spawing including the spawn count, the max spawn count and giving the new robots an index. The game mode also stores an array of spawn characters. This is a singleplayer game. Be aware in a multiplayer game, the game mode would only exist on the server, not the clients
The same functionality as at game start (see below) can be triggered when the player "prints" a new robot.
if the amount of spawn characters is >= the max amount robots we allow....
...tell the first robot in the list to dissolve itself and remove him from our array of spawned characters
...always add the new spawned robot to the array and increase the spawn counter.
Try to find a spawn pad to spawn our robots.
We complain. The game will not be playable.
If not, we check all actors in the scene. If that has the bool IsStartSpawnPad set to true, we save that as active. (if more than one has it set, the last in that list will be taken here)
Do we have a valid reference. Then take that!
If we found one, we take that, if not...
If not we take the first one in the list, if there is none...
Disable old spawnpad
Set new spawnpad
When a bot overlaps with a spawnpad, set that as the new active spawnpad and disable the previous one.
Tell the game instance to save the game data
Tell the HUD that hot spawned in the player controller to display "saving" on the UI
Return that it was a success
